WEBVTT

00:40.457 --> 00:43.501
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, GROUPS, AND
ORGANIZATIONS IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

00:43.585 --> 00:46.379
SCENES WITH ANIMALS ARE STAGED
ACCORDING TO ANIMAL WELFARE GUIDELINES

00:49.632 --> 00:50.842
Is it okay

00:51.843 --> 00:53.386
if I ask you a question?

00:54.512 --> 00:55.555
Go ahead.

00:56.806 --> 01:00.852
Did Officer Kwak ever tell you
about the footage of Geun-ho

01:00.935 --> 01:03.938
coming into the billiard club in the past?

01:04.481 --> 01:06.191
Geun-ho came to the billiard club?

01:07.484 --> 01:09.110
No, he said nothing of the sort.

01:09.694 --> 01:10.653
Really?

01:12.947 --> 01:15.116
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

01:15.200 --> 01:17.452
Mu-cheol is always watching the CCTV

01:17.535 --> 01:19.162
but he hasn't said anything like that.

01:20.371 --> 01:21.915
I wonder why he never mentioned that.

01:24.542 --> 01:25.668
If I may ask,

01:25.752 --> 01:29.172
what's the relationship between
Mr. Kwak's family and Dae-bum's family?

01:30.757 --> 01:32.050
Their relationship…

01:33.468 --> 01:34.886
They do have some history.

01:35.386 --> 01:37.555
I only heard this from the others.

01:37.639 --> 01:41.309
Apparently, Mr. Kwak and Dae-bum's father
were best friends

01:41.392 --> 01:43.853
until that incident in this building.

01:43.937 --> 01:47.816
Ever since then,
they became sworn enemies.

01:49.192 --> 01:50.151
Why?

01:51.194 --> 01:53.613
On the day of the incident,

01:53.696 --> 01:56.241
Dae-bum's father said
he went fishing with Mr. Kwak

01:56.324 --> 01:57.992
but Mr. Kwak denied it.

01:58.910 --> 02:00.203
That testimony

02:00.286 --> 02:05.458
was the final blow that made
Dae-bum's father the culprit.

02:06.167 --> 02:09.963
Could you tell me how old
Officer Kwak was back then?

02:10.463 --> 02:13.216
-What did you say?
-I didn't do it.

02:13.299 --> 02:14.884
This is a police station, you punks.

02:14.968 --> 02:16.386
I was…

02:16.970 --> 02:18.471
I was 11 years old.

02:18.555 --> 02:21.558
And Mu-cheol is
four years older than I am.

02:21.641 --> 02:24.185
So he must have been in his
second year of middle school.

02:24.269 --> 02:25.979
ANGOK MIDDLE SCHOOL

02:26.062 --> 02:28.022
Calm down, breathe.

02:28.106 --> 02:29.566
KWAK MU-CHEOL

02:29.649 --> 02:31.734
Kwak Mu-cheol from Angok Middle School.

02:38.324 --> 02:39.784
You killed her, didn't you?

02:41.619 --> 02:42.787
My sister.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.916
What are you so afraid of?

02:48.167 --> 02:49.335
What?

02:50.587 --> 02:53.673
What do you want to hide so badly
that you'd even commit murder?

02:54.340 --> 02:55.592
In this building…

02:57.385 --> 02:58.720
you murdered my…

02:59.596 --> 03:00.680
Dae-bum.

03:02.098 --> 03:03.308
What are you saying?

03:04.475 --> 03:05.560
It's not me.

03:05.643 --> 03:07.562
How can you do that to her?

03:11.149 --> 03:13.484
How can you do that to my family?

03:18.823 --> 03:19.991
It's not me.

03:20.074 --> 03:21.492
It's not me!

03:29.584 --> 03:31.628
Did you think I would never find out?

03:34.631 --> 03:36.424
Did you think you could just live on

03:37.258 --> 03:38.718
without anyone finding out?

03:38.801 --> 03:40.303
It's not me.

03:40.386 --> 03:41.721
I didn't do it!

03:41.804 --> 03:44.057
I said I didn't do it!

03:44.849 --> 03:46.893
Did you kill Ms. Jung to cover up

03:48.353 --> 03:50.855
the fact that your son killed Seon-a?

03:51.856 --> 03:54.984
You're making absurd accusations.

03:55.068 --> 03:56.611
Then what's this?

03:56.694 --> 03:59.155
What does this graffiti mean?

03:59.739 --> 04:02.450
You know better than I do
as to what Geun-ho saw that day.

04:03.117 --> 04:04.702
How dare you run your mouth!

04:04.786 --> 04:06.746
It's over for you.

04:07.497 --> 04:10.124
This is just graffiti,
but what would the experts say?

04:10.708 --> 04:13.711
How dare you blackmail me
with some stupid graffiti?

04:13.795 --> 04:15.421
Then what about the CCTV footage?

04:16.506 --> 04:19.550
Did you think no one would see
if he stayed at the end of the stairs?

04:19.634 --> 04:22.929
I bet you didn't even think about
the reflections on Geun-ho's window.

04:23.513 --> 04:24.347
Geun-ho.

04:25.181 --> 04:26.015
Get up here.

04:29.310 --> 04:30.478
Hey.

04:30.561 --> 04:31.938
Come on already.

04:33.815 --> 04:36.651
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

04:44.450 --> 04:45.660
I'm right, aren't I?

04:45.743 --> 04:48.913
You killed Ms. Jung
to cover up for killing Seon-a!

04:48.997 --> 04:50.331
Stop talking nonsense!

04:51.165 --> 04:52.166
You don't know anything.

04:55.586 --> 04:58.089
Everyone will now know

04:58.172 --> 04:59.966
that your son is a murderer!

05:03.261 --> 05:04.429
You're wrong.

05:06.639 --> 05:09.517
You've got it all wrong.

05:15.231 --> 05:16.691
Bom's grandmother

05:17.442 --> 05:19.736
wasn't murdered by my son.

05:20.486 --> 05:21.904
It was me.

05:24.824 --> 05:27.827
I mean, shit. I wasn't planning on it.

05:30.621 --> 05:32.790
But it should have been you.

05:32.874 --> 05:34.667
It should have been you there!

06:04.280 --> 06:06.074
Please start driving.

06:06.157 --> 06:07.575
Where to?

06:07.658 --> 06:09.202
Myeongju Police Station.

06:09.285 --> 06:11.329
Hey, stop right there.

06:11.412 --> 06:13.247
-Hurry and drive, please.
-Wait.

06:13.331 --> 06:14.874
Hey, hold on!

06:16.918 --> 06:18.044
Damn it.

06:20.046 --> 06:21.464
I'm on my way.

06:22.048 --> 06:24.967
I'm going there with evidence
for a murder case.

06:37.730 --> 06:38.856
What's that?

06:41.067 --> 06:42.276
Don't stop the car, okay?

06:42.360 --> 06:44.028
-Vehicle 386,
-Please keep going.

06:44.112 --> 06:45.571
stop the car.

06:45.655 --> 06:47.865
-But the cop is telling us to stop.
-No.

06:47.949 --> 06:49.659
-Please just keep going.
-Stop the car.

06:49.742 --> 06:51.285
-Stop the car!
-Please.

06:51.369 --> 06:52.370
Just trust me.

06:52.453 --> 06:54.038
I'm going to the station anyway.

06:54.122 --> 06:55.748
Stop the car right now.

06:58.126 --> 06:59.544
Sir, please.

07:12.306 --> 07:13.641
Please I beg you.

07:17.770 --> 07:19.147
Get out of the car.

07:19.230 --> 07:20.314
Get out!

07:21.607 --> 07:23.025
-Get out!
-Trust me this once.

07:23.109 --> 07:24.610
I said get out!

07:24.694 --> 07:25.945
Hey, open the door.

07:26.529 --> 07:27.488
Hey!

07:28.197 --> 07:29.157
Get out.

07:29.657 --> 07:30.741
Hey!

07:35.997 --> 07:38.416
How dare he talk like that
to a tax-paying citizen like me?

07:39.000 --> 07:40.543
Hold tight.

07:40.626 --> 07:41.669
All right?

07:42.420 --> 07:43.421
Thank you.

07:44.005 --> 07:47.383
Hey! I'm telling you I didn't do it!

07:55.266 --> 07:56.767
VIOLENT CRIMES TEAM 1

07:56.851 --> 07:58.019
KWAK MU-CHEOL

08:15.578 --> 08:16.662
Geun-ho remembered

08:17.413 --> 08:18.789
what happened in the past

08:18.873 --> 08:21.167
watching the footage Dae-bum recorded…

08:21.918 --> 08:23.461
No, Seon-a!

08:23.544 --> 08:25.922
-Run away, it hurts!
-Geun-ho.

08:26.589 --> 08:27.757
One.

08:30.885 --> 08:31.928
Two.

08:35.056 --> 08:36.766
…and he began to talk.

08:48.861 --> 08:52.490
…wasn't murdered by my son. It was me.

08:53.074 --> 08:55.409
You're saying Mr. Kwak said this, right?

08:55.493 --> 08:56.327
Yes.

08:56.827 --> 08:59.163
He's the father of Officer Kwak
of Angok Precinct.

08:59.789 --> 09:03.125
You know that secret recordings
can't be used in court, right?

09:03.751 --> 09:05.753
You might even get punished for this.

09:05.836 --> 09:08.130
I'm the victim here.

09:08.214 --> 09:09.549
Sure, whatever.

09:09.632 --> 09:11.092
I've been tricked by her.

09:11.175 --> 09:13.469
Those two are trying to frame me.

09:13.553 --> 09:14.428
Just you wait.

09:14.512 --> 09:16.180
I won't let this slide.

09:16.264 --> 09:17.473
Sir.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.100
-I get it, let go!
-Move.

09:19.183 --> 09:21.018
Who's the one that killed Ms. Jung?

09:26.857 --> 09:28.776
Who killed Seon-a?

09:33.239 --> 09:35.074
As we expected,

09:35.700 --> 09:39.704
Mr. Kwak and Officer Kwak
were the culprits of the incidents.

09:42.123 --> 09:45.501
It's what Geun-ho has been trying
to tell everyone for a long time.

09:51.507 --> 09:54.302
How did you manage
to get a confession out of Mr. Kwak?

09:55.636 --> 09:56.721
I don't know.

09:57.221 --> 10:01.100
I wasn't in my right mind,
so I didn't even know what I was saying.

10:02.059 --> 10:05.813
If it wasn't for the taser
you bought for me,

10:05.896 --> 10:07.398
I would've been in big trouble.

10:10.109 --> 10:13.070
Actually, the bit about seeing
Mu-cheol on the window

10:13.154 --> 10:16.907
of Geun-ho's house was a lie.

10:17.408 --> 10:21.454
I have no idea what made me say that.

10:22.121 --> 10:25.499
Why didn't you fight back?

10:28.586 --> 10:30.087
Well, earlier…

10:30.796 --> 10:32.798
I wasn't in my right mind either.

10:36.969 --> 10:40.681
I wonder why Geun-ho only
wrote down parts of his name.

10:41.641 --> 10:44.769
If he had spelled it out,
the culprit would've been caught already.

11:02.787 --> 11:06.332
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

11:22.848 --> 11:24.392
Did my dad come by here?

11:25.184 --> 11:26.977
He went fishing with my dad.

11:27.645 --> 11:28.729
I see.

11:33.526 --> 11:35.945
I heard you've been bragging
about solving hard problems.

11:39.698 --> 11:41.784
Stop acting like you're studying.

11:42.410 --> 11:43.452
Give it back.

11:44.078 --> 11:46.372
My dad always scolds me because of you.

11:51.001 --> 11:52.169
What an idiot.

11:55.673 --> 11:56.549
Hey.

11:56.632 --> 11:58.509
What did you just say?

11:58.592 --> 12:00.761
If you're dumb, at least be nice.

12:00.845 --> 12:01.887
You insolent little…

12:04.432 --> 12:05.599
Hey.

12:05.683 --> 12:07.935
You can brag all you want on television.

12:08.018 --> 12:10.563
How dare you call me an idiot
just because you're smart?

12:10.646 --> 12:12.356
Hey, get up.

12:13.023 --> 12:14.150
Hey!

12:50.728 --> 12:54.148
KWAK MU-CHEOL

13:36.273 --> 13:39.318
I'm sorry I've been gone
for so long, Gyeo-ul.

13:46.075 --> 13:48.702
Yeo-reum, I have somewhere to go tomorrow.

13:50.371 --> 13:52.665
Do you want to stay here while I'm gone?

13:54.625 --> 13:56.585
It won't take long.

14:00.756 --> 14:03.008
Okay, I'll do that.

14:07.680 --> 14:10.391
ALTTEUL STORE

14:12.393 --> 14:14.478
I guess you can't really know someone.

14:14.562 --> 14:17.481
That Kwak family ruined our building.

14:18.148 --> 14:19.316
Tell me about it.

14:19.400 --> 14:21.652
The world is a scary place.

14:21.735 --> 14:25.656
Mu-cheol became a cop
after doing something so terrible.

14:25.739 --> 14:27.408
Gosh, it's scary.

14:27.491 --> 14:30.119
This whole thing must have been
tough for Chang-su's family.

14:30.828 --> 14:32.538
Take good care of them.

14:33.581 --> 14:35.416
You feel responsible, don't you?

14:36.250 --> 14:38.460
I decided to sell them the building.

14:38.544 --> 14:39.795
What?

14:40.546 --> 14:42.089
You're going to sell it to Chang-su?

14:42.172 --> 14:43.757
Chang-su is willing to buy that?

14:43.841 --> 14:47.011
I told him it was half-price.
Anyone would buy it.

14:49.388 --> 14:50.222
Dad.

14:50.306 --> 14:52.892
That's so awesome of you.
What a great decision.

14:53.475 --> 14:55.185
Even I'm thankful.

14:55.269 --> 14:56.520
You idiot.

14:56.604 --> 14:58.647
Why would you be thankful?

14:59.273 --> 15:01.942
Man, you're stupid.

15:06.405 --> 15:07.823
Hello.

15:07.907 --> 15:10.159
Welcome. It's been tough, right?

15:10.242 --> 15:11.285
It's nothing.

15:11.827 --> 15:14.914
Forget about it all and cheer up, okay?

15:14.997 --> 15:16.290
Thank you.

15:18.876 --> 15:20.669
Hey, Yeo-reum. Take a seat.

15:21.921 --> 15:23.464
What brings you here?

15:24.298 --> 15:25.341
Well…

15:26.425 --> 15:29.011
The things you gave me for the house.

15:29.094 --> 15:32.222
I think you're going to
have to take it back.

15:33.515 --> 15:35.559
Are you moving out of the billiard club?

15:35.643 --> 15:36.644
Yes.

15:36.727 --> 15:39.980
I just heard that Chang-su
is going to buy that building.

15:41.357 --> 15:43.359
-That's great.
-I know, right?

15:43.943 --> 15:48.447
From where you stand,
I'm sure you're sick of this town

15:48.530 --> 15:51.325
and want to leave as soon as possible,

15:52.284 --> 15:54.662
but I'm a bit sad to see you go.

15:56.372 --> 15:57.498
Same here.

15:58.123 --> 16:01.126
Actually, Bom would be sadder than I am.

16:01.835 --> 16:02.878
I mean…

16:03.545 --> 16:04.838
You know Jeong-hun, right?

16:05.714 --> 16:09.927
He got into trouble again,
so I'm sure it's been tough on Bom.

16:11.637 --> 16:14.390
Did something happen to her?

16:15.557 --> 16:16.934
Yes, do that.

16:18.018 --> 16:19.103
Hey, you.

16:19.728 --> 16:21.730
-Yes, sir.
-Take this to the third floor.

16:22.356 --> 16:23.357
Yes, sir.

16:23.440 --> 16:25.609
Take it easy. Do you have some left?

16:39.665 --> 16:42.668
Where is the bag that was here?

16:42.751 --> 16:43.836
It was just here.

16:45.045 --> 16:48.340
This site is a fucking mess.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.217
Hey, Kim!

16:50.968 --> 16:52.469
What are you doing?

16:53.220 --> 16:54.221
Excuse me?

16:54.304 --> 16:56.765
Why are you taking that bag upstairs?

16:56.849 --> 16:59.351
You told me to put it here.

16:59.435 --> 17:00.394
I did?

17:01.103 --> 17:03.313
You fucking imbecile.

17:03.397 --> 17:06.191
Why would you take that upstairs?

17:06.275 --> 17:07.818
We have to use them down here!

17:07.901 --> 17:10.487
-But…
-Hurry up and bring them down!

17:11.989 --> 17:13.240
Yes, sir. I'm sorry!

17:21.248 --> 17:22.583
Take a look at this guy.

17:23.292 --> 17:24.626
Look how old he is.

17:25.502 --> 17:27.296
You poor bastard.

17:30.674 --> 17:31.717
Hey.

17:31.800 --> 17:34.011
Wait for Dad to do that. It'll get cold.

17:34.094 --> 17:35.137
Oh, right.

17:37.931 --> 17:39.308
The rice is cooked well though.

17:41.518 --> 17:43.020
Have some, Kim.

17:43.937 --> 17:45.564
I'll be right back.

17:47.900 --> 17:49.276
Help yourselves.

17:49.860 --> 17:51.653
I thought you wouldn't come.

17:53.447 --> 17:54.907
Sir, let me pour you one.

18:04.750 --> 18:06.126
Forget about earlier.

18:08.295 --> 18:11.673
I can't say that
I'm satisfied with your work,

18:13.258 --> 18:15.344
but you can come to work next month too.

18:18.847 --> 18:20.808
Don't be like that and just drink.

18:20.891 --> 18:23.227
He's letting you off the hook so much.

18:23.310 --> 18:25.145
Don't drink if you don't want to.

18:30.692 --> 18:31.819
Let me pour you one, sir.

18:50.087 --> 18:51.964
So you can drink after all.

18:52.047 --> 18:54.341
Here, let me pour you one more.

19:22.202 --> 19:23.245
Bom.

19:23.871 --> 19:25.747
I think Dad stopped by last night.

19:26.790 --> 19:27.708
Bom.

19:29.543 --> 19:30.586
Bom.

19:34.256 --> 19:36.216
Jeong-hun gambled again.

19:36.300 --> 19:39.052
He left with those people
with all the money.

19:46.018 --> 19:47.102
Bom.

19:47.811 --> 19:48.896
Bom.

19:50.647 --> 19:51.648
Ha-neul.

20:00.908 --> 20:01.909
Bom.

20:54.878 --> 20:55.963
Ha-neul.

20:58.382 --> 20:59.466
Yeo-reum.

21:02.135 --> 21:03.804
Where are you coming back from?

21:05.555 --> 21:07.349
I've been working these days.

21:07.933 --> 21:09.476
What about school?

21:11.853 --> 21:13.397
What brings you here?

21:13.981 --> 21:15.274
What about Bom?

21:16.692 --> 21:17.776
Bom?

21:19.069 --> 21:21.488
She went to see you yesterday.

21:22.906 --> 21:24.157
You didn't meet her?

21:24.783 --> 21:25.742
To see me?

21:27.035 --> 21:28.912
She didn't contact me.

21:33.917 --> 21:35.252
When did she go out?

21:36.920 --> 21:38.588
Yesterday morning.

21:41.550 --> 21:42.634
Ha-neul.

21:43.176 --> 21:45.887
Go to the station and report her missing.

21:46.888 --> 21:49.308
And check the places she might have gone.

21:51.893 --> 21:52.894
Yeo-reum.

21:54.021 --> 21:55.314
I'll look for her too.

21:55.939 --> 21:56.773
Let's go.

21:58.358 --> 21:59.443
Come on.

22:08.827 --> 22:11.330
Be well, Bom.

22:11.413 --> 22:13.332
I…

22:15.250 --> 22:16.918
Please put on your seatbelts,

22:17.002 --> 22:20.547
and please enable airplane mode
on your phones.

22:21.089 --> 22:24.718
You can store your belongings
in the overhead bin or below your seat.

22:24.801 --> 22:26.094
Thank you.

22:50.744 --> 22:51.787
Father.

23:12.808 --> 23:14.017
Ms. Jung.

23:15.352 --> 23:17.729
Please help us find Bom.

23:17.813 --> 23:20.857
Please watch over Bom
so she doesn't make any rash decisions.

23:22.275 --> 23:23.318
I beg you.

23:23.401 --> 23:24.820
JUNG YEONG-SUK

23:42.712 --> 23:44.422
I was wrong, Father.

23:57.018 --> 23:58.145
I'm sorry.

24:24.087 --> 24:27.257
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

24:39.352 --> 24:40.353
Bom.

24:40.437 --> 24:41.605
Bom!

24:44.900 --> 24:46.484
Bom.

24:47.194 --> 24:48.403
Please wake up.

25:09.716 --> 25:12.385
Bom, wake up.

25:13.303 --> 25:15.222
Please wake up.

25:19.017 --> 25:20.268
Are you okay?

25:21.019 --> 25:23.021
-Yeo-reum.
-Bom.

25:23.104 --> 25:24.189
-Yeo-reum.
-It's okay.

25:28.193 --> 25:30.195
Yeo-reum.

25:30.779 --> 25:31.947
It's okay.

25:34.574 --> 25:36.618
I'm so sorry.

25:39.037 --> 25:41.706
It's all right.

25:42.874 --> 25:44.668
Yeo-reum.

25:45.168 --> 25:46.753
It's okay.

25:50.590 --> 25:51.675
It's okay.

25:52.550 --> 25:53.885
You're okay.

26:38.263 --> 26:42.726
Dae-bum had the same look
on his face as Bom that day.

26:44.811 --> 26:47.063
It felt like I saw him at his lowest.

27:02.704 --> 27:05.832
I decided to stay in Angok.

27:06.333 --> 27:08.126
And I decided to start working.

27:10.837 --> 27:14.215
I make 50,000 won a day
working 4 and a half hours.

27:14.299 --> 27:16.176
And I work six days a week.

27:17.385 --> 27:19.929
My work begins at 4:00 a.m.

27:26.186 --> 27:27.437
Oh, my gosh.

27:31.816 --> 27:35.028
At first, it wasn't easy
to wake up early in the morning.

27:35.111 --> 27:37.781
-But that's the best part of my work now.
-Good morning.

27:38.365 --> 27:39.449
Thank you.

27:39.532 --> 27:40.867
Here, take this.

27:41.368 --> 27:43.244
-Thank you.
-Sure.

27:43.328 --> 27:47.540
While the dusky night sky
may seem bleak at the end of the day,

27:48.041 --> 27:51.294
the very same sky
is invigorating at the beginning of a day.

27:53.505 --> 27:57.258
It's hard to believe
that they're one and the same sky.

28:02.138 --> 28:04.557
When I'm done with work, it's 8:30 a.m.

28:05.350 --> 28:08.520
From that time,
I have the whole day to myself.

28:10.230 --> 28:13.108
I work less, and I earn time.

28:20.532 --> 28:23.993
I'm living in Bom's house on rent.

28:29.582 --> 28:31.543
I still have some money left to spend

28:32.293 --> 28:34.712
after the 300,000 won rent
and the living expenses.

28:34.796 --> 28:36.840
So I've been saving up as well.

28:39.259 --> 28:42.303
After Bom and Ha-neul leave for school,

28:42.387 --> 28:45.598
I go to the library every day.

28:46.182 --> 28:49.811
You have to upload that
before you leave work every day.

28:49.894 --> 28:52.522
How many times do I have to tell you
that you can't put off

28:52.605 --> 28:54.524
book rental logs for a week?

28:54.607 --> 28:58.903
But Ji-yeong, that lady is the only one
who comes to this library.

28:58.987 --> 29:01.072
So why bother doing it daily?

29:01.781 --> 29:03.700
You're pretty mouthy for a public servant.

29:03.783 --> 29:05.577
Gosh. This stupid countryside.

29:14.627 --> 29:15.754
Ma'am?

29:20.967 --> 29:22.677
Where's the real estate office here?

29:25.221 --> 29:26.681
Please don't call me "ma'am."

29:33.229 --> 29:35.482
I've been hooked on transcription lately,

29:35.565 --> 29:37.901
so I've been transcribing
my favorite book.

29:39.027 --> 29:43.281
I feel like it clears out my mind
and fills up my heart.

29:45.492 --> 29:48.578
After leaving the library,
I jog with Dae-bum.

29:49.537 --> 29:53.875
Dae-bum changed his jogging schedule
from morning to evening because of me.

29:54.876 --> 29:57.962
We like to talk while jogging.

29:58.046 --> 29:59.088
Remember last time?

29:59.172 --> 30:00.757
Our daily lives may be simple,

30:00.840 --> 30:03.218
but we never run out of topics
to talk about.

30:03.301 --> 30:05.512
I almost feel like Dae-bum talks

30:05.595 --> 30:07.347
more than I do these days.

30:07.430 --> 30:08.848
It feels easier than it used to.

30:08.932 --> 30:10.850
I think you run better than I do now.

30:10.934 --> 30:12.727
That may well be true.

30:24.322 --> 30:28.201
Dae-bum started working
with Professor Holland again.

30:31.454 --> 30:35.416
Professor Holland offered him
to work together in a relaxed environment,

30:35.500 --> 30:37.752
saying he puts his family before work.

30:37.836 --> 30:39.629
Dae-bum was touched,

30:39.712 --> 30:41.422
so he decided to work with him.

30:43.716 --> 30:48.596
He says it feels like Holland is
teaching him how to approach work.

31:12.829 --> 31:14.122
-Yeo-reum.
-Yes?

31:14.205 --> 31:17.542
There's something I want to do with you.

31:17.625 --> 31:18.751
What is it?

31:19.627 --> 31:23.673
But can you promise me first
that you'll do this with me?

31:23.756 --> 31:26.926
I don't think I can do it alone.

31:27.802 --> 31:29.387
Why are you getting all serious?

31:29.971 --> 31:31.598
Don't fall for it. Just ignore her.

31:32.807 --> 31:33.933
It's…

31:38.438 --> 31:39.480
It's this.

31:41.524 --> 31:42.692
What is this?

31:42.775 --> 31:45.904
HONGS.COM COMICS WEBTOON CONTEST

31:46.696 --> 31:49.157
-Webtoon contest?
-Yes.

31:49.240 --> 31:51.367
But this is the real juice.

31:51.451 --> 31:53.328
The first place gets 100 million won.

31:53.411 --> 31:54.621
It's huge, right?

31:55.288 --> 31:57.665
But why would you do this with me?

31:57.749 --> 32:01.377
Look. I can kind of draw,
but I can't write.

32:01.461 --> 32:04.839
But you've worked at a publishing company
and read lots of books.

32:04.923 --> 32:07.133
You can write, and I can--

32:07.216 --> 32:08.384
No way.

32:08.885 --> 32:11.804
You know how scared I get about writing.

32:11.888 --> 32:13.556
Yeo-reum, please.

32:13.640 --> 32:17.060
You wrote that interview
with the old lady with Dae-bum.

32:17.143 --> 32:20.521
But that's totally different from this.

32:20.605 --> 32:22.857
Just ignore her.
She's just got her head in the clouds.

32:22.941 --> 32:24.484
You can't even draw that well.

32:24.567 --> 32:26.861
You little brat. You don't know anything.

32:26.945 --> 32:28.196
I'll wash the dishes.

32:28.279 --> 32:29.238
Seriously.

32:29.322 --> 32:32.075
-I beg you, Yeo-reum. Let's just try.
-Come on, Gyeo-ul.

32:32.158 --> 32:33.868
-Just this once.
-I can't.

32:33.952 --> 32:35.995
-Just eat.
-Come on.

32:36.079 --> 32:38.039
I beg you, ma'am. Please work with me.

32:39.791 --> 32:42.669
You're being weird, Ji-yeong.
Why do you eat here these days?

32:43.962 --> 32:46.214
And can't you call me before coming?

32:46.297 --> 32:49.217
Then I would bring more food.

32:49.926 --> 32:51.302
This is fine.

32:53.096 --> 32:54.305
I got a house in Seoul.

32:54.389 --> 32:56.683
So I just need to move there.

32:57.558 --> 33:00.103
Are you here to ask me to help you pack?

33:00.186 --> 33:01.396
Pack what?

33:05.024 --> 33:09.737
I got the truck and the boxes
ready to help you pack up.

33:09.821 --> 33:10.989
So don't worry.

33:12.115 --> 33:14.617
Hey, I wasn't even thinking of that.

33:18.830 --> 33:20.456
We're sharing this food, you know.

33:22.041 --> 33:23.001
Sorry.

33:23.835 --> 33:25.253
You're better than your dad.

33:26.129 --> 33:28.923
-Hello.
-Hey, you were having dinner together.

33:29.007 --> 33:29.966
Hey.

33:30.883 --> 33:33.136
-Seong-min, actually…
-What?

33:33.219 --> 33:35.513
-Do you need help with something?
-That's not it.

33:35.596 --> 33:39.851
I was wondering if I could
get the billiard club girl's number.

33:40.435 --> 33:41.519
Yeo-reum?

33:42.562 --> 33:45.565
I'm glad you're here too, Ms. Cho.

33:45.648 --> 33:49.235
Please give this message to Dae-bum.

33:49.318 --> 33:51.362
What message?

33:51.988 --> 33:56.993
I didn't even get to
thank those two properly.

33:57.076 --> 34:01.539
So I was meaning to treat them
to dinner at my restaurant.

34:01.622 --> 34:02.957
Oh, really?

34:03.041 --> 34:04.667
That's a fantastic idea.

34:04.751 --> 34:07.545
But while you're treating them,

34:07.628 --> 34:09.922
could you treat everyone properly?

34:10.506 --> 34:11.924
How?

34:12.008 --> 34:13.301
Beef.

34:13.384 --> 34:14.844
Beef!

34:14.927 --> 34:16.596
-Beef!
-Beef!

34:16.679 --> 34:18.097
-Beef!
-Beef!

34:18.181 --> 34:19.932
Jun, come over for beef, okay?

34:21.726 --> 34:23.186
All right. Tell me her number, okay?

34:23.269 --> 34:24.687
-Goodbye.
-Bye.

34:28.733 --> 34:29.567
Yeo-reum.

34:29.650 --> 34:31.652
Then let's take Ha-neul with us.

34:32.278 --> 34:33.780
Ha-neul? Why would you take him?

34:33.863 --> 34:36.616
-He can stay and study.
-Why not?

34:37.158 --> 34:39.243
He didn't come with us
to the valley last time.

34:39.327 --> 34:41.245
He'd probably rather study.

34:41.329 --> 34:42.288
Oh, right.

34:42.872 --> 34:44.290
-Bom.
-Yes?

34:45.041 --> 34:46.209
Do you…

34:47.293 --> 34:49.170
not talk to Jae-hun anymore?

34:50.713 --> 34:51.798
I mean…

34:53.758 --> 34:56.469
I was so surprised when I got this text.

34:58.763 --> 35:02.642
YEO-REUM, I'M GOING BACK TO THE STATES.
PLEASE TAKE CARE OF BOM.

35:06.312 --> 35:09.148
I don't know what happened
between you two,

35:09.899 --> 35:12.026
but Jae-hun really likes you.

35:14.028 --> 35:15.029
You know that, right?

35:16.280 --> 35:17.865
Stop talking about him.

35:20.034 --> 35:21.077
Okay.

35:24.872 --> 35:26.040
Yeo-reum.

35:26.124 --> 35:29.544
I hope we win the contest
and win the 100 million won.

35:30.211 --> 35:32.380
What will you do with that money?

35:40.429 --> 35:42.056
I miss Grandma.

35:56.571 --> 35:59.240
If Bom draws her webtoon
based on my writing,

35:59.824 --> 36:01.284
It'll be a total failure.

36:01.367 --> 36:02.410
Come on.

36:02.910 --> 36:05.830
My writing is horrific. You know that.

36:06.497 --> 36:07.957
I'm not sure I do.

36:09.458 --> 36:10.626
Come on.

36:10.710 --> 36:13.421
GIFT
ANGOK PUBLIC LIBRARY

36:14.005 --> 36:18.134
If I'm being honest,
I think we are very much alike.

36:19.302 --> 36:20.678
How so?

36:21.554 --> 36:25.349
I'm always so nervous and afraid
when I'm solving math problems.

36:26.684 --> 36:28.644
But one day, Professor Holland

36:29.395 --> 36:31.689
got a question incorrect and he just said,

36:34.275 --> 36:35.610
He just shook it off.

36:35.693 --> 36:36.736
Really?

36:39.906 --> 36:41.157
You know,

36:42.575 --> 36:45.328
I really love talking
about these kinds of things with you.

36:51.584 --> 36:54.670
So I decided to try writing.

36:55.671 --> 36:57.381
Why can't I think of anything?

36:59.884 --> 37:01.010
Gyeo-ul.

37:01.761 --> 37:05.056
I'll end up having leukophobia.

37:11.020 --> 37:13.731
But as expected, it was difficult.

37:14.315 --> 37:16.442
What do I do?

37:19.320 --> 37:20.488
What?

37:20.571 --> 37:22.990
No one's expecting a masterpiece,
so just do it?

37:26.327 --> 37:27.411
You're right.

37:28.621 --> 37:30.164
How did you know?

37:32.083 --> 37:33.042
All right.

37:38.673 --> 37:40.841
I'm going to end up
in Hollywood at this rate.

37:47.306 --> 37:49.308
I'm going nowhere with this.

37:50.434 --> 37:52.728
Bom, I'm sorry!

37:54.647 --> 37:56.190
Can I check these out?

37:57.191 --> 37:58.192
Sure.

38:01.070 --> 38:03.239
I'm not a genius.

38:03.906 --> 38:06.367
I need to acknowledge that first.

38:08.786 --> 38:10.663
I'm just an ordinary person.

38:10.746 --> 38:13.833
Actually, I might even be a bit lacking.

38:16.877 --> 38:19.213
Writing every day.

38:19.297 --> 38:22.508
There's nothing else I can do
except for that.

38:29.432 --> 38:31.309
-Gosh, you surprised me!
-What's this?

38:31.392 --> 38:32.518
When did you come home?

38:32.601 --> 38:34.103
Gosh, look at you.

38:34.186 --> 38:36.355
And you were complaining
that you can't write.

38:36.439 --> 38:38.691
You didn't read it, did you?

38:39.942 --> 38:42.194
But isn't the lady too old?

38:42.278 --> 38:44.530
How am I supposed to draw a mom?

38:44.613 --> 38:48.075
This is just a rough draft, okay?

38:48.159 --> 38:50.369
-So it's not final.
-Let me read some more.

38:50.453 --> 38:51.704
No, you can't.

38:51.787 --> 38:52.997
-Come on.
-Someone's here.

38:53.831 --> 38:54.999
Who could it be?

38:56.625 --> 38:58.002
Who is it?

39:02.840 --> 39:04.008
Jae-hun.

39:04.925 --> 39:05.885
Heo Jae-hun.

39:05.968 --> 39:07.595
Bom. Yeo-reum.

39:09.263 --> 39:10.473
Have you been well?

39:10.973 --> 39:12.767
Didn't you go back to the States?

39:13.768 --> 39:14.810
I did.

39:15.728 --> 39:16.896
But…

39:18.064 --> 39:20.316
I kept thinking about it.

39:20.399 --> 39:21.400
Wait.

39:21.484 --> 39:23.486
So you came back from the states?

39:23.569 --> 39:24.779
That's right.

39:25.404 --> 39:26.614
I see.

39:27.656 --> 39:29.200
Anyway, I kept thinking

39:29.784 --> 39:32.745
about myself while I wasn't with you--

39:32.828 --> 39:34.455
Have you lost your mind?

39:34.538 --> 39:36.290
It's not a trip downtown.

39:36.374 --> 39:38.626
Do you even know
how much the plane ticket costs?

39:38.709 --> 39:42.046
Can you please let me finish?
Stop cutting me off.

39:42.838 --> 39:44.965
Fine. My bad.

39:46.300 --> 39:49.637
I thought deeply about my life.

39:49.720 --> 39:51.889
About what I truly want,

39:52.640 --> 39:55.518
and about what I live for.

39:56.394 --> 39:59.313
And at the end of that thought,
I ended up here.

40:00.689 --> 40:02.900
Really? Why?

40:04.318 --> 40:05.528
To marry you.

40:05.611 --> 40:06.654
What?

40:08.114 --> 40:10.741
Marry me? Are you crazy?

40:11.492 --> 40:12.493
Bom.

40:12.993 --> 40:15.246
Be honest with me.

40:15.329 --> 40:17.456
Should I just go back to the States?

40:19.708 --> 40:20.626
Hey.

40:21.168 --> 40:23.838
We're not even old enough to marry.

40:24.338 --> 40:25.881
I'm serious about this.

40:27.133 --> 40:28.843
Stop beating around the bush
and answer me.

40:31.387 --> 40:33.389
Do you hate that I'm here?

40:34.807 --> 40:37.184
I mean, I don't hate it, but…

40:39.061 --> 40:44.066
We should at least go out first
before discussing marriage.

40:44.150 --> 40:45.067
I see.

40:45.985 --> 40:47.403
Should we do that then?

40:48.195 --> 40:50.156
I wasn't saying
we should get married right away.

40:51.115 --> 40:52.700
Again with the damn jokes.

40:52.783 --> 40:54.410
Do you have a death wish?

40:56.454 --> 40:57.580
Jae-hun.

40:58.789 --> 41:00.040
Welcome back.

41:00.624 --> 41:01.709
Yeo-reum.

41:03.210 --> 41:05.296
-I'm glad you're here.
-Thank you.

41:11.844 --> 41:12.928
I missed you.

41:14.096 --> 41:15.723
Fine, me too.

41:15.806 --> 41:16.932
Gyeo-ul, I'm home.

41:22.021 --> 41:23.272
Who is this guy?

41:23.772 --> 41:25.149
Hello.

41:25.232 --> 41:27.109
I'm your brother-in-law.

41:28.194 --> 41:30.154
What did you just say?
You need to shut up.

41:30.237 --> 41:31.572
What are you talking about?

41:32.531 --> 41:33.407
My brother-in-law.

41:34.700 --> 41:36.785
Stop it unless you want to die.

41:36.869 --> 41:38.746
Gosh.

41:38.829 --> 41:40.998
-Is it good?
-It's so juicy.

41:41.081 --> 41:43.042
Beef always tastes good.

41:45.586 --> 41:46.629
Dae-bum!

41:47.171 --> 41:48.631
-We're here.
-Yeo-reum!

41:48.714 --> 41:50.090
-Hurry up and sit.
-Hello.

41:50.174 --> 41:52.218
Everyone, take your seats.

41:52.301 --> 41:53.761
You must be starving.

41:53.844 --> 41:55.721
-Thank you so much.
-We have more.

41:55.804 --> 41:57.932
-Jun, sit down.
-There's so much food.

41:58.015 --> 41:59.225
Right, Jun.

42:00.100 --> 42:02.520
Geun-ho is going to school now.

42:02.603 --> 42:03.812
What? No way.

42:05.231 --> 42:06.690
He's finally going to school.

42:06.774 --> 42:08.108
Congratulations.

42:08.192 --> 42:10.236
This is the good stuff.
Look at the marbling on this meat.

42:10.319 --> 42:11.904
Dig in.

42:11.987 --> 42:13.781
Geun-ho, come and eat.

42:13.864 --> 42:14.782
Yeo-reum.

42:14.865 --> 42:16.200
-Dae-bum.
-Yes?

42:16.283 --> 42:19.787
I'm so grateful to the two of you.

42:20.829 --> 42:22.122
It's nothing.

42:22.206 --> 42:23.374
Gosh.

42:23.457 --> 42:25.209
Please help yourselves.

42:25.292 --> 42:26.710
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

42:26.794 --> 42:28.420
-Help yourselves.
-Thank you for the food.

42:28.504 --> 42:30.506
-Thank you for the food.
-Mr. Bae.

42:30.589 --> 42:31.465
What?

42:31.549 --> 42:34.552
Aren't we hosting this party
for Yeo-reum and Dae-bum?

42:36.011 --> 42:37.096
What's that?

42:37.846 --> 42:39.515
Come on!

42:39.598 --> 42:42.768
It's nice to celebrate
this good news with everyone.

42:42.851 --> 42:44.353
Why don't we read it?

42:44.436 --> 42:45.396
"Congratulations,

42:45.980 --> 42:47.231
on making it to Seoul!"

42:47.314 --> 42:49.942
"Ms. Cho Ji-yeong!"

42:50.025 --> 42:52.820
She finally leaves Angok!

42:52.903 --> 42:54.405
-What's wrong with him?
-What's wrong with him?

42:55.990 --> 42:57.157
Jun!

42:57.741 --> 42:58.826
Make sure you eat a lot!

42:58.909 --> 43:01.161
Okay, I'll eat a lot.
Thank you for the food!

43:02.246 --> 43:03.789
-Shall we eat too?
-Thank you for the food.

43:03.872 --> 43:05.165
Thank you for the food.

43:05.249 --> 43:07.334
-Enjoy.
-You want a wrap?

43:08.544 --> 43:09.670
This is so good.

43:10.713 --> 43:12.339
Eat it before it gets cold.

43:17.720 --> 43:18.887
-Thank you.
-Enjoy.

43:18.971 --> 43:20.180
All right.

43:20.264 --> 43:22.933
-Go, Jun!
-So cute.

43:27.855 --> 43:29.481
-So adorable.
-Come here.

43:30.357 --> 43:32.693
Way to go!

43:32.776 --> 43:34.570
Come on, Ji-yeong.

43:52.588 --> 43:54.840
I thought about what happiness is.

43:57.009 --> 43:58.594
I looked it up in the dictionary.

43:59.303 --> 44:03.432
Happiness is a state
of being pleased, fulfilled,

44:03.515 --> 44:06.352
and content in life.

44:08.646 --> 44:12.858
I found that definition to be too long,
so I decided to make it shorter.

44:14.902 --> 44:15.986
Happiness.

44:17.446 --> 44:19.531
The state of being sufficient.

44:25.913 --> 44:28.207
I looked back on what happened today.

44:29.124 --> 44:31.794
I biked through the cold breeze
of the early morning

44:31.877 --> 44:35.255
to my heart's content before sunrise.

44:35.339 --> 44:36.548
I was pleased.

44:38.217 --> 44:39.343
It was sufficient.

44:45.641 --> 44:48.644
I came back home thirsty and drank water.

44:50.104 --> 44:54.108
It reminded me of what Ms. Jung said,
that water is the most delicious.

44:57.111 --> 44:58.195
That indeed was true.

44:58.904 --> 45:00.030
It was sufficient.

45:05.619 --> 45:07.496
When I'm hanging my laundry,

45:07.579 --> 45:09.623
I like the sound of my clothes clapping.

45:10.749 --> 45:14.461
And I like the lingering smell
of detergent on my hands.

45:15.295 --> 45:16.463
It was sufficient.

45:23.053 --> 45:26.557
I dozed off at the library

45:26.640 --> 45:28.934
thanks to the hypnotic afternoon sunlight.

45:29.017 --> 45:30.811
It was a sweet nap.

45:31.311 --> 45:32.396
It was sufficient.

45:34.773 --> 45:36.191
It's always fun

45:36.275 --> 45:40.279
standing in front of the shelves,
choosing what to read.

45:41.155 --> 45:42.239
It's exciting.

45:42.322 --> 45:44.616
THE ELEGANT TRUTH
BY KIM SEONG-HYEON

45:44.700 --> 45:45.784
It was sufficient.

45:51.582 --> 45:54.543
When I'm lying down
with Bom to go to sleep,

45:54.626 --> 45:57.045
I always laugh so hard my stomach hurts.

45:57.713 --> 46:00.299
Sometimes, just staring
at each other makes us laugh.

46:01.341 --> 46:03.677
It was sufficient.

46:06.096 --> 46:07.973
Stop doing that.

46:15.022 --> 46:16.064
Bom.

46:16.148 --> 46:17.149
Bom.

46:22.196 --> 46:23.363
It's okay.

46:25.115 --> 46:26.950
Bom told me…

46:27.034 --> 46:27.993
You're fine.

46:28.076 --> 46:30.996
… that when I consoled her that day,

46:31.622 --> 46:36.084
she somehow felt like
everything was going to be fine.

46:37.544 --> 46:38.754
That's how I felt too.

46:39.421 --> 46:41.507
After I said
that everything was going to be fine,

46:41.590 --> 46:45.385
I really felt like everything
was going to be fine.

46:49.973 --> 46:51.141
Feel that breeze.

46:52.351 --> 46:54.937
It really feels like
autumn now, doesn' it?

46:55.020 --> 46:56.021
It really does.

46:57.689 --> 46:59.441
Do you want to hear something cool?

46:59.942 --> 47:00.859
What is it?

47:02.819 --> 47:03.904
Bom as in spring,

47:04.613 --> 47:05.739
Yeo-reum as in summer,

47:06.990 --> 47:08.492
-autumn, the season,
-Autumn, the season,

47:08.575 --> 47:09.660
-And Gyeo-ul, as in winter!
-And Gyeo-ul!

47:09.743 --> 47:12.204
-You're right.
-We have all four seasons with us.

47:23.006 --> 47:24.049
Goodbye.

47:25.384 --> 47:28.637
My first summer in Angok.

47:38.981 --> 47:41.191
This feels so weird.

47:46.363 --> 47:48.574
Do you not feel anything when I'm leaving?

47:50.117 --> 47:51.159
Ji-yeong.

47:51.243 --> 47:54.913
Waiting for you is practically
my hobby and expertise now.

47:56.331 --> 47:58.041
Until I go out with another guy.

47:59.751 --> 48:01.086
If you want to, you should.

48:01.169 --> 48:02.588
Seriously?

48:03.755 --> 48:06.258
You can't live without tormenting people.

48:06.341 --> 48:09.011
You'll never find a guy
who is as fun to torment as I am.

48:09.511 --> 48:11.430
I only do that with you.

48:11.513 --> 48:12.973
I never do that to others.

48:13.932 --> 48:16.476
No one else in this world
makes me as angry as you.

48:17.936 --> 48:20.397
Or you could go off the market
and come back like I did.

48:20.480 --> 48:22.149
My heart will stay the same.

48:25.068 --> 48:26.194
Back from where?

48:30.574 --> 48:31.992
Have you lost your mind?

48:32.075 --> 48:34.536
-Hey.
-You've completely lost it.

48:35.120 --> 48:37.706
-You're going to wake him up.
-Don't say that in front of him.

48:37.789 --> 48:39.249
Take it back!

48:43.295 --> 48:44.588
You woke him up.

48:44.671 --> 48:47.549
-This is your fault!
-My goodness.

48:55.057 --> 48:56.933
What are you doing on your day off?

48:57.851 --> 48:59.645
Why? Did you find something else to eat?

49:00.145 --> 49:02.731
No, let's go see Dae-ho.

49:04.024 --> 49:05.359
What? Dae-ho?

49:06.777 --> 49:08.904
You said I should be friends with him.

49:09.488 --> 49:10.906
Look at you, all grown up.

49:12.449 --> 49:13.533
Here.

49:17.120 --> 49:18.205
What was that?

49:18.288 --> 49:21.041
I wanted to try refusing you once.

49:21.124 --> 49:23.001
Gosh, that felt good.

49:23.710 --> 49:25.879
How dare you refuse me?

49:25.962 --> 49:27.714
You think you can get away with that?

49:28.465 --> 49:30.509
-It's so much fun.
-Come here!

49:30.592 --> 49:32.427
Gyeo-ul, go bite him!

49:32.511 --> 49:34.054
Hey, give him back!

49:34.137 --> 49:35.889
-Jae-hun, come here!
-Catch him!

49:35.972 --> 49:39.017
Gyeo-ul, go bite him now!
Let's teach him a lesson.

49:39.101 --> 49:40.894
Gyeo-ul, look at this!

49:40.977 --> 49:42.062
Gosh.

49:42.145 --> 49:43.271
Stop it!

49:43.355 --> 49:45.607
-Dae-bum.
-Yes?

49:46.692 --> 49:49.611
Do you regret staying here at all?

49:51.029 --> 49:52.155
I don't.

49:53.532 --> 49:54.991
What about you?

49:57.744 --> 49:58.787
Me neither.

50:21.184 --> 50:22.436
My life is

50:23.186 --> 50:24.479
truly sufficient.

50:25.689 --> 50:29.443
I haven't quite figured out
how I should go on,

50:30.694 --> 50:33.572
but my life is sufficient.

50:34.990 --> 50:36.158
Let's live this life.

51:45.519 --> 51:50.524
Subtitle translation by: Jea-Heon Chung
